      <section xml:id="sec-Advancedlearningobjectives13">
        <title>Advanced learning objectives</title>

        <p>
          In addition to mastering the basic objectives, here are the tasks you should be able 
          to perform, with practice:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
      Justify separation using the chain rule and substitution rather than informal manipulation of <m>dy/dx</m>. 
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
      Identify and include singular or special solutions (such as <m>y=0</m>) that arise when dividing by <m>g(y)</m>.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
      Recognize when the resulting integrals lead to solutions that must remain in implicit form and verify such solutions by differentiation.
            </p>
          </li>

        </ul>

      </section>


